What you need to know:

Sheng has been described as a variation of English infused with Swahili phonology spoken by middle-to-lower class students in universities to differentiate themselves from students from upcountry.The fast innovation of new words makes the language not ideal as a language for a grammar school.The language is mainly grown in Nairobi, with different parts of the city producing different words or versions of the same word. Despite its closeness to Kiswahili, English has had more influence on the language's vocabulary.